          <td bgcolor="" valign="top" width="1"><img src="/lotr/gfx/trans_header1.gif" width="0" height="2" vspace="0" hspace="0" border="0"></td>
          <td bgcolor="" valign="top"><!-- #BeginEditable "Body" --> 
            <table width=100% border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0>
<tr><td width=1><img src="/lotr/gfx/mom/gre_01.gif" width=6 height=6></td><td width=100% background="/lotr/gfx/mom/gre_02.gif"></td>
<td width=1><img src="/lotr/gfx/mom/gre_03.gif" width=6 height=6></td></tr>
<tr><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/gre_04.gif"><img src="/lotr/gfx/mom/clear.gif" height=35 width=1></td>
<td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/gre_05.gif" class="headerbg"><font class="h1font"><font color="#FFFFFF"><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 border=0 width=100%><TR><td><font class="h1font">Tournament Reports</td><form method='post' action=''><td align='right' valign='bottom'><select name='select' onChange='go(this)'><option selected>More DeckTech Tournament Reports</option><option value='#'> </option><option value='/swccg/treports/index.php3'>Star Wars: CCG</option><option value='/lotr/treports/treports.php'>Lord of the Rings</option><option value='/magination/treports/treports.php'>Magi-Nation Duel</option><option value='/swtcg/treports/treports.php'>Star Wars TCG</option></select></td></form></tr></table></font></B></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/gre_06.gif"></td></tr>
	<tr><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_07.gif"></td>
		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> Pittsburgh, PA 2-16-2002<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(4.62)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=400'>R. "Voice of Law" Smith</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=400&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> February 26, 2002</font><p align='justify'><blockquote><font class="bfont"> There hadn&#39;t been a SWCCG tournament in Pittsburgh in months. I was pumped for this one at Helm&#39;s Deep Games and had spent a few hours perfecting my decks. For LS I was playing standard WYS and for DS it was a teched-out Court mains with the Rancor.<br>
<br>
I grab a bagel at the 7-11 and make the hour drive into the city. Get there about five minutes late to find that I am one of three players who showed up. Great. I go across the street to CVS to pick up some RX Memory Tea and when I get back the other two SW players have absconded, and the would-be tournament director has joined the concurrent LOTR tourney!! I am sorely disappointed, but vow not to let my driving and preparation go to waste. I have no LOTR deck, so I join the tourney with my SWCCG decks.<br>
<br>
Game 1<br>
My Court vs. Fred Lewis (kid) and his modified Gandalf starter.<br>
Yeah so his deck is basically the starter with all the rares he owned thrown in, and the shadow mixed around to include some Uruks. He starts Gandalf and Green Dragon Inn. My 3 starting effects (as always) are All Wrapped Up, IAO/Secret Plans, and Mobilization Points. I am dark side so I go first, pull Mara Jade with the Audience Chamber, Executor DBay with IAO and Death Star 2 DBay with the Court objective. He goes and pulls Sam to remove some burdens and double-moves to the Council Courtyard. I drain, pull Mara&#39;s saber, then Elis Helrot Mara in front of his guys and drop IG-88 with Riot Gun to join the fray. IG gets lucky and draws a 5 (Twilek Advisor) to capture Frodo and he gives up the Ring to Sam. Mara swings at Gandalf and misses, and the kid plays Servant of the Secret Fire to make Mara power -3 so Gandalf overwhelms her. I move Iggy back to the Audience Chamber and flip my objective.<br>
<br>
He goes and puts a bunch or Uruk-Hai in front of IG-88 but then I remind him that Iggy is a droid so he cannot be battled. He puts Glamdring on Gandalf and moves only once to the Mithril Mine.<br>
<br>
I go and get the Rancor Pit with the Rancor out. Drop the Cantina from hand and put Mighty Jabba in there with Ref 3 Fett, then a Presence of the Force to add to the drain. Move Iggy in to the Pit and Frodo becomes an E.L. Hobbit cookie for the Rancor. I retrieve a bunch and he loses a bunch.<br>
<br>
He goes and starts moving his big group of Uruk-Hai over to the Cantina to stop the drain, but I dont think they&#39;ll get there in time to make a difference. He double-moves to the next sanctuary and it&#39;s my turn.<br>
<br>
EPP Vader and EPP Maul come down to square off with Gandalf and little Sam. Vader hits Sam and Maul hits Gandalf (on the second try). He wants to play Intimidate to prevent the wound on Sam but I Sense it. That turns out to be the game-winning maneuver seeing as how Sam was already exhausted from removing Frodo&#39;s burdens earlier on. Sam dies and Vader wears the Ring.<br>
<br>
FW by 23 thanks to Rancor retrieval<br>
<br>
<br>
Game 2 WYS vs. Scott Staple&#39;s I have more money than I know what to do with Nazgul<br>
Yeah he&#39;s playing 4 Witch-Kings and 3 Pale Blades and 4 Morgul Gates etc...<br>
Anyway he starts Arwen and Legolas, and first turn double-moves to the Ford of Bruinen.<br>
<br>
I get a great hand and get Theron Nett in ship with a Cannon to the system and Melas down to the Cantina to flip.<br>
He puts Ulaire Attea in front of Melas but I just Dodge it. He double-moves again to Tha Bridge.<br>
<br>
I get a bunch of Force seeing as how he&#39;s at the Bridge, I&#39;m flipped, and I started Staging Areas. I drain at the system and Docking Bay 94 (where Melas Dodged to). Deploy Chewbacca, Enraged in front of the Fellowship with a Ralltiir Freighter Captain to help. Then I put Talon Karrde and EPP Han in front of Attea, drop Ill Take The Leader to add to Melas&#39; drain, EPP Luke to DBay 94, and battle. Run Luke Run! brings Luke in on the party and Attea gets punked for a good 22 in battle damage (my 3 BDs were all 5s). Chewie and the RFC battle the Fellowship and it is determined that he cannot use Legolas&#39; aimed archery against my guys because they are not minions. I take the one point of archery on Chewie. Battle destinies leave him with a dead Arwen, an exhausted Legolas, and a twice-wounded Frodo (Chewie was P.O.&#39;ed, what can I say). I lose the RFC.<br>
<br>
He goes and plays Morgul Gay-tes for the Witch-King down at the Cantina with the Pale Blade. Battles me with the Witch-King and overwhelms Talon Karrde. Luke and Han remain for the fierce battle and Han bites the dust. He moves the Fellowship to site 6 and stays because he needs to heal. Draws up and thanks to the damage he suffered in that one battle he is almost out of cards.<br>
<br>
I go and drain him for 1 and 2 and that wipes out his deck. I On The Edge Luke with a tracked Bith Shuffle and get back four cards. Deploy a Bacta Tank, then put another Han with Chewie and battle the Fellowship again. Legolas bites it and Frodo takes 6 burdens from Isildur&#39;s Bane. Almost there! Han goes to the Tank.<br>
<br>
His turn and there&#39;s not much he can do but add a Morgul Blade to the Witch-King and battle again. Luke dies and I Houjix the rest of the damage. He double-moves to site 8 but I don&#39;t think that will be good enough, because...<br>
<br>
My turn I drain him for the rest of his hand, then put a spare copy of Luke down with Chewie to finish off little Frodo. Full win by 14<br>
<br>
I go take a piss and as I exit the john I am greeted by the pairing announcements...my Court vs. Jim Li...whaddya know.<br>
<br>
So as is typical on tournament Saturdays in Pittsburgh, Jim has shown up with the latest, greatest deck he got from his buddies online. And as is also typical, he has decimated every random.kid and their random.kid.decks that he has played. So I know that if I don&#39;t beat him...no one will.<br>
<br>
Unfortunately I cannot give you too many details about this game, as Jim wishes for his newest, most &quot;broken&quot; deck to be kept secret as much as possible. So I&#39;ll just hit you with a few highlights.<br>
<br>
-I Monnoked him early for two Orc Bowmen and three Durin&#39;s Secrets...that was huge.<br>
<br>
-He tried to deploy a Uruk Spy against my lone Ephant Mon generating force at the Executor DBay, but then I reminded him that no spies may deploy to same site as Ephant.<br>
<br>
-I had the Rancor all ready to eat his Pippin, but he dropped the Cave Troll with his Hammer to kill the Rancor and set Pippin free. Dammit!<br>
<br>
-I used 4-LOM to cancel the text of his Frodo (thus canceling his resistance), but Jim had a Sam out and passed the Ring to him. Then on his next turn he wanted to transfer the Ring back to Frodo, and I figured that should be allowed.<br>
<br>
-He used Sleep, Caradhras to knock out all my effects, which really screwed me for force gen for a while.<br>
<br>
-I think the game-winning move for me was grabbing his Servant of the Secret Fire with There&#39;ll Be Hell To Pay. After that his Fellowship had serious trouble putting up a fight against my EPP Vaders and Mauls.<br>
<br>
FW by 2<br>
<br>
Game 4<br>
my WYS vs. Daniel Rocco&#39;s Twilight Denial variant<br>
His deck was somewhat like the standard twilight denial deck, but with more Fellowship added in (including Boromir). So I wasn&#39;t sure if I was going to be able to kill off his Frodo in time.<br>
<br>
Luckily for me, he got a bad draw (or so he claimed), and the only guys I saw from him for the first two turns were Aragorn (he started with) and Pippin. I quickly sent Phylo Gandish over to deal with Pippin and set up drains at the Tatooine system (Dash in the Outrider) and in the Cantina (Melas by himself with a Dodge and a Houjix in hand). Meanwhile I tried to set up a big beatdown in hand, but I could not seem to find an EPP Han.<br>
<br>
On his third turn he dropped a crapload of Moria minions on my Melas, and I had to Dodge out of that. He followed out to the Docking Bay with half of them and left half inside the Cantina to drain. I finally activated a Han, so I Tunnel Visioned for it and brought my hand to the following: EPP Luke, EPP Han, Chewie Enraged, Don&#39;t Get C0cky, Run Luke Run!, and a bunch of other stuff. I had to decide between:<br>
A. Putting all my guys on Tatooine to clear out the Moria minions, or<br>
B. Going for the kill against Aragorn and Frodo.<br>
I went with B, momentarily forgetting about Aragorn and his defender +1 gametext. So Aragorn blocked all 3 of my guys and then bit the dust. But at least I had Luke, Han, and Chewie there in front of Frodo for next turn.<br>
<br>
He went and drained me in the Cantina and then fought my Melas again - I had no choice but to lose Melas and Houjix. Then he put out Boromir with an Armor and the Blade of Gondor and double-moved to site 5. My turn.<br>
<br>
I drained him at the system and played Tunnel Vision from lost to get a Projection of a Skywalker for the Cantina. Then I dropped a Ralltiir Freighter Captain with Luke, Han, and Chewie and battled his Fellowship. He played some interrupt to make Boromir defender +1 and picked up Luke and Chewie with that. Han and the RFC were not enough to defeat Frodo, in fact they got beat thanks to Frodo being armed with Sting. Luke swung and missed Boromir, Han shot and hit Frodo, so Frodo took a wound and even with all my battle destinies Boromir only had to take one wound because of his Armor. I lost the RFC.<br>
<br>
His turn, he drained with the Moria guys then dropped two Athelas and healed Boromir and Frodo. Then he double-moved again, bringing him to site 7. My turn.<br>
<br>
I knew I had to stop him here, so I drained then put Talon Karrde down with the rest of my guys and battled the Fellowship again. He played another defender +1 interrupt for Boromir, so the Lord of Gondor squared off with Luke and Chewie for the second turn in a row. Han and Talon faced off with Frodo - he played Hobbit Intuition to add 3 to Frodo&#39;s power, again beating my two smugglers. That&#39;s annoying. Boromir took his wound and I was all out of options. His turn he double-moved to site 9 and won the game.<br>
<br>
Full loss with 12 cards left<br>
<br>
<br>
So I get second place in the tournament, Jim gets first. I win 5 packs of LOTR and give them away. I heard one of them had a foil Arwen in it...oh well =)<br>
<br>
Hope you enjoyed my report. If you are wondering the relevance of all this, just refer to these two questions:<br>
1. Do I have too much time on my hands? (answer: no, just insomnia)<br>
2. Are writing and CCGs two of my hobbies? (answer: yes)<br>
<br>
